description: COBBLE AFTER STD.14 DUE TO LESS INTERBILLET TIME. (1C+1H).
problem_description: COBBLE AFTER STD.14 DUE TO LESS INTERBILLET TIME. (1C+1H).
one_year: 1. COBBLE AT STAND-14 EXIT , MATERIAL CAME OUT INBETWEEN CVR-1 AND STAND-14
two_year: 2 METRE PIECE CARRYN FORWARD FROM SHEAR-1
three_year: TWO METRE PIECE CUT DURING GAP CHOP INBETWEEN TWO BILLETS
four_year: INTERBILLET GAP 1.1 SECOND BECAUSE ONE BILLET TAKEN FOR TRIAL (150MM)  AND SIMULTANEOUSLY  ROLLING STARTED FOR 165MM BILLET IN AUTO MODE
five_year: DUE TO THIS BILLET CAME IN VERY CLOSE GAP , SH1 TAKEN TAIL CUT FOR LAST BILLET TAIL AND GONE FOR GAP CHOP FOR NEXT BILLET ,TILL THAT TIME BILLET HEAD ENTERED 2METRE  DURING GAP CHOP
corrective_action:
1. COBBLE REMOVED 
2. DURING ANY START OF MILL FOR NEW SECTION OR TRIAL , OPERATOR SHOULD CALL FIRST BILLET MANUALLY AND PUT IN AUTO MODE WITH MORE INTERBILLET TIME BY OBSERVING THE ROLLING TIME
3. IN ANY CASE IF BILLET COME CLOSER OPERATOR SHOULD START CHOPPING MANUALLY THE NEXT BILLET (3 TO 4 CUTS)
preventive_action:
1. OPERATOR TO BE TRAINED ABOUT THE LOGIC OF BILLET CALL 
2. PROPER KNOWLEDGE TO BE THERE ABOUT ROLLING TIME OF DIFFERENT SIZES OF BILLET
3. FIRST BILLET TO BE CALLED MANUAL CALL
4. BEFORE PUTTING BILLET CALL IN AUTO INTERBILLET TIME TO BE INCREASED DURING START OF ROLLING
